From: Andreas Gruenbacher <agruen@suse.de>
Subject: Don't write anything to the in-inode xattr space of reserved inodes

We are not using the in-inode space for xattrs in reserved inodes because
mkfs.ext3 doesn't initialize it properly. Make sure that we also don't
overwrite the i_extra_isize field in that case. This is for cleanliness
only, and doesn't fix an actual bug.

Signed-off-by: Andreas Gruenbacher <agruen@suse.de>

Index: linux-2.6.11-rc1-mm2/fs/ext3/inode.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.11-rc1-mm2.orig/fs/ext3/inode.c
+++ linux-2.6.11-rc1-mm2/fs/ext3/inode.c
@@ -2653,7 +2653,7 @@ static int ext3_do_update_inode(handle_t
 	} else for (block = 0; block < EXT3_N_BLOCKS; block++)
 		raw_inode->i_block[block] = ei->i_data[block];
 
-	if (EXT3_INODE_SIZE(inode->i_sb) > EXT3_GOOD_OLD_INODE_SIZE)
+	if (ei->i_extra_isize)
 		raw_inode->i_extra_isize = cpu_to_le16(ei->i_extra_isize);
 
 	BUFFER_TRACE(bh, "call ext3_journal_dirty_metadata");
